<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-05-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-05-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="214" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                        <head>No. 214.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bassett</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                        of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-05-16"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 16,
                                1872</date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 103.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatches numbered 120, 122, and 123
                            have been received. For the views of this Department respecting the
                            indignity offered to the consular officer of the United States at Saint
                            Marc, to which you revert in your dispatch No. 123, you are referred to
                            my instruction No. 101, of the 3d instant.</p>
                        <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>